### Relay Execute — single HTTP request via notx relay engine
### POST /v1/relay/execute
###
### Prerequisites:
###   1. notx server running on localhost:4060
###   2. A registered + approved device with URN notx:device:<uuid>
###      Set the X-Device-ID header to your device URN.
###
### The relay engine will:
###   - Validate your device identity
###   - Check the target URL against the security policy
###   - Execute the outbound HTTP request server-side
###   - Return the upstream response

POST http://localhost:4060/v1/relay/execute
Content-Type: application/json
X-Device-ID: notx:device:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

{
  "request": {
    "method": "GET",
    "url": "https://httpbin.org/get",
    "headers": {
      "Accept": "application/json"
    }
  }
}

###
### Example with variable interpolation
### Variables in {{double_braces}} are resolved before the request is sent.

POST http://localhost:4060/v1/relay/execute
Content-Type: application/json
X-Device-ID: notx:device:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

{
  "variables": {
    "api_host": "httpbin.org",
    "endpoint": "json"
  },
  "request": {
    "method": "GET",
    "url": "https://{{api_host}}/{{endpoint}}",
    "headers": {
      "Accept": "application/json",
      "X-Request-Source": "notx-relay"
    }
  }
}

###
### POST request with a JSON body

POST http://localhost:4060/v1/relay/execute
Content-Type: application/json
X-Device-ID: notx:device:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

{
  "variables": {
    "api_url": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "content_type": "application/json"
  },
  "request": {
    "method": "POST",
    "url": "{{api_url}}",
    "headers": {
      "Content-Type": "{{content_type}}"
    },
    "body": "{\"hello\": \"from notx relay\"}"
  }
}
